  "result": "The fix is clean and complete. Here's a summary of the changes made:\n\n## Summary\n\n**Root cause:** The `parseSourcesToFileScheme` function in `TemplateManager.kt` used Jsoup to parse HTML and then re-serialize it via `doc.body().html()`. When source URL substitutions were made (e.g., rewriting `img src` to `file://` scheme), the Jsoup re-serialization would strip or mangle `<script>` tags and their contents. This broke complex card templates that rely on inline JavaScript, such as the \"Enhanced Cloze\" addon.\n\n**Fix:** Replaced the Jsoup-based HTML parsing with a regex-based approach that only modifies the specific `src`/`data` attributes on `img`, `video`, `audio`, `source`, and `object` tags. The rest of the HTML content (including `<script>` tags) is left completely untouched.\n\n**Changes in `AnkiDroid/src/main/java/com/ichi2/libanki/TemplateManager.kt`:**\n\n1. Removed Jsoup imports (`org.jsoup.Jsoup` and `org.jsoup.nodes.Document.OutputSettings`)\n2. Rewrote `parseSourcesToFileScheme` to use regex matching instead of Jsoup parsing:\n   - A tag-level regex matches `<img>`, `<video>`, `<audio>`, `<source>`, and `<object>` tags\n   - An attribute-level regex finds the `src` or `data` attribute value within each matched tag\n   - Only the specific attribute value is replaced; everything else is preserved as-is\n   - Tag and attribute names are lowercased in the output (matching Jsoup's behavior)\n\n**Secondary fix:** The original code used `||` (short-circuiting OR) to chain `replaceWithFileScheme` calls, meaning if one tag type had changes, other tag types wouldn't be processed. The new single-pass regex approach processes all matching tags correctly.",
